1️⃣ PERCENTAGES – FOUNDATION (Placement Level)

🔹 What are Percentages?

A percentage means "per hundred" or "out of 100."

The symbol % represents percent.

For example:

50% means 50 out of 100

25% means 25 out of 100

100% means the whole quantity


Percentages are used to compare values, calculate profit/loss, discounts, marks, interest, taxes, and data analysis.

Percentage questions test:

Calculation ability

Logical thinking

Speed and accuracy


These are one of the most frequently asked topics in placement aptitude tests.


---

🔹 Understanding Percentages

Example 1

A student scores 80 marks out of 100.

Percentage

= (80/100) × 100

= 80%


---

Example 2

Out of 200 students, 50 are girls.

Percentage of girls

= (50/200) × 100

= 25%


---

🔹 Percentage Formula (Must Remember)

Formula 1

Percentage = (Part / Whole) × 100

Example:

30 students passed out of 40.

Percentage

= (30/40) × 100

= 75%


---

Formula 2

Part = (Percentage × Whole) / 100

Example:

20% of 300

= (20 × 300)/100

= 60


---

Formula 3

Whole = (Part × 100) / Percentage

Example:

30 is 15% of what number?

Whole

= (30 × 100)/15

= 200


