🔹 Important Tricks (Placement Shortcuts)

Trick 1

Remember common percentages.

50% = Half

25% = One-fourth

75% = Three-fourths

10% = One-tenth

20% = One-fifth


---

Trick 2

Finding 15%

15%

= 10% + 5%

Example:

15% of 200

= 20 + 10

= 30


---

Trick 3

Finding 35%

35%

= 30% + 5%

Example:

35% of 400

= 120 + 20

= 140


---

Trick 4

To increase a number by x%

New Value = Original × (100 + x)/100

Example:

Increase 500 by 20%

= 500 × 120/100

= 600


---

Trick 5

To decrease a number by x%

New Value = Original × (100 − x)/100

Example:

Decrease 800 by 25%

= 800 × 75/100

= 600


---

⚠️ Common Mistakes

Do not forget to multiply by 100 when calculating percentages.

Read the question carefully to identify the whole and the part.

Convert percentages to fractions whenever possible for faster calculations.

Do not confuse percentage increase with percentage of a number.



